\section{Authentication and configuration}

The Stay A While API now mixes two authentication styles.
The API-key management endpoints rely on the ordinary KTH browser login flow,
while the queue endpoints still accept token authentication.
We therefore reuse the shared authenticated browser session from [[ladok3]]
and only look up an API key when a token-authenticated endpoint needs one.
The defaults follow the public service.
<<the Stay A While base URL>>=
"https://queue.eecs.kth.se"
<<constants>>=
CONFIG_API_KEY = "stayawhile.api_key"
CONFIG_BASE_URL = "stayawhile.base_url"
@

The API key should still be easy to supply both interactively and in scripts.
We first check the environment variable [[STAYAWHILE_API_KEY]].
If it is absent, we fall back to [[typerconf]].
<<helper functions>>=
def get_api_key():
  """Return the configured Stay A While API key."""
  try:
    return os.environ["STAYAWHILE_API_KEY"]
  except KeyError:
    pass

  try:
    return typerconf.get(CONFIG_API_KEY)
  except KeyError:
    raise ValueError(
         "missing Stay A While API key; set STAYAWHILE_API_KEY or run "
         "kthutils config stayawhile.api_key --set <your-api-key>")


def find_api_key():
  """Return the configured Stay A While API key, when available."""
  try:
    return get_api_key()
  except ValueError:
    return None
